## Downstream Use Instructions

When this projection is used by SplitEpic:

- Treat this projection as the strategic decomposition frame.
- Treat the split epic proposal as the opportunity to partition.
- Treat repository evidence as current implementation reality.
- Preserve the full original strategic opportunity.
- Partition by strategic capability responsibility.
- Use repository evidence to discover natural boundaries.
- Derive explicit dependency relationships.
- Ensure each resulting initiative has independent strategic value.
- Prove complete coverage.
- Prevent overlap and duplicate ownership.
- Block splitting if the partition would create task fragments.
- Hand each resulting initiative to the standard new-epic authoring model.
- Do not modify the roadmap.
- Do not update roadmap completion context.
- Do not generate implementation tasks.
- Do not create file-level plans.
- Do not generate code.
- Do not create execution prompts.

## Projection Integrity Checklist

Before finalizing, verify:

- The projection contains strategic decomposition semantics only.
- No split epic proposal is included.
- No repository state is included.
- No roadmap completion state is included.
- No completed epic history is included.
- No resulting epic is authored.
- Every retained statement helps partition one strategic opportunity into coherent initiatives.
- Every major retained statement traces to the Project Context or is clearly marked projection-local.
- Opportunity conservation rules are explicit.
- Capability partitioning rules are explicit.
- Repository boundary discovery rules are explicit.
- Dependency derivation rules are explicit.
- Split quality criteria are explicit.
- Coverage rules are explicit.
- Overlap prevention rules are explicit.
- Split blocking rules are explicit.
- Handoff requirements are explicit but do not duplicate CreateNewEpic authoring semantics.
- Canonical vocabulary is preserved.
- Excluded operational, implementation, authoring, validation, realignment, reimagination, and prioritization details are not present.
- The projection is compact enough to be passed into SplitEpic.
